WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.586 --> 00:00:03.820
<i>Previously</i>
<i>on</i> Will Trent...

2
00:00:03.955 --> 00:00:05.422
I had this bad feeling
you weren't really sick.

3
00:00:05.555 --> 00:00:09.093
-FBI share any new intel
with you?
-Not yet.

4
00:00:09.227 --> 00:00:11.661
<i>You are The Commander.</i>

5
00:00:12.864 --> 00:00:15.365
<i>Le Bon Nosh. 8:00 p.m.</i>

6
00:00:15.498 --> 00:00:17.168
Don't you look handsome?

7
00:00:17.301 --> 00:00:19.136
Damn it. watch your step.

8
00:00:19.270 --> 00:00:20.905
<i>I've left you a little present.</i>

9
00:00:21.038 --> 00:00:23.007
Adelaide. what did you do?

10
00:00:23.140 --> 00:00:24.708
<i>But you had to go</i>
<i>and ruin it by having your boss</i>
<i>go looking for me.</i>

11
00:00:24.841 --> 00:00:27.912
<i>I know exactly what</i>
<i>it feels like to be the reason</i>

12
00:00:28.045 --> 00:00:30.314
<i>your loved ones end up</i>
<i>in harm's way.</i>

13
00:00:30.847 --> 00:00:33.017
<i>Shame. Guilt. Anger.</i>

14
00:00:33.150 --> 00:00:34.252
Amanda. No.

15
00:00:35.853 --> 00:00:37.387
Help!

16
00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:45.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

17
00:01:14.457 --> 00:01:16.260
Will. we got to
get Amanda out of here.

18
00:01:17.895 --> 00:01:19.096
Let the techs do their job.

19
00:01:35.545 --> 00:01:38.082
-How was the body
when you found it?
-The body?

20
00:01:38.983 --> 00:01:41.319
This is Deputy Director
Amanda Wagner.

21
00:01:43.753 --> 00:01:44.922
She was on her back.

22
00:01:45.056 --> 00:01:47.258
Understood. Special Agent.

23
00:01:47.391 --> 00:01:49.260
Just-- Please.

24
00:01:54.597 --> 00:01:56.100
This is as bad as it gets.

25
00:02:00.304 --> 00:02:01.838
Oh. Wags.

26
00:02:03.807 --> 00:02:06.043
We're gonna get
the son of a bitch
who did this.

27
00:02:11.514 --> 00:02:13.351
Wait. Okay. wait. let me.

28
00:02:13.483 --> 00:02:14.852
- Let me.
- Okay.

29
00:02:54.291 --> 00:02:57.328
The Lord is my shepherd.
I shall not want.

30
00:02:59.330 --> 00:03:00.797
<i>He restoreth my soul.</i>

31
00:03:03.833 --> 00:03:08.072
<i>He leadeth me</i>
<i>in the paths of righteousness</i>
<i>for his name's sake.</i>

32
00:03:09.173 --> 00:03:13.010
<i>Yea. though I walk</i>
<i>through the valley</i>
<i>of the shadow of death.</i>

33
00:03:13.543 --> 00:03:15.279
<i>I will fear no evil.</i>

34
00:03:16.646 --> 00:03:18.015
<i>For thou art with me.</i>

35
00:03:18.149 --> 00:03:21.185
<i>Thy rod and thy staff.</i>
<i>they comfort me.</i>

36
00:03:23.020 --> 00:03:27.757
<i>Surely goodness</i>
<i>and mercy shall follow me</i>
<i>all the days of my life.</i>

37
00:03:27.892 --> 00:03:30.760
<i>and I will dwell in the house</i>
<i>of the Lord forever.</i>

38
00:03:33.097 --> 00:03:34.265
<i>Amen.</i>

39
00:04:07.364 --> 00:04:08.399
Mom.

40
00:04:22.546 --> 00:04:23.613
Oh.

41
00:04:24.848 --> 00:04:26.283
Caroline. I need your help.

42
00:04:26.417 --> 00:04:28.886
Yes. sir.

43
00:04:29.019 --> 00:04:33.157
I need you to access
Amanda's calendar.
computer. everything.

44
00:04:34.058 --> 00:04:36.994
I wanna know what she was doing
leading up to last night. okay?

45
00:04:37.128 --> 00:04:38.929
Yeah. you got it.

46
00:04:45.835 --> 00:04:46.904
Oh.

47
00:04:48.572 --> 00:04:50.441
Thank you.

48
00:04:52.476 --> 00:04:54.245
Oh. boy. Uh...

49
00:04:55.645 --> 00:04:59.416
No! Don't you dare go in there!
You have no damn shame. do you?

50
00:04:59.550 --> 00:05:02.186
- That's not what I was doing.
-  -You couldn't wait for this.

51
00:05:02.319 --> 00:05:04.288
Amanda knew that
you were after her job.

52
00:05:04.421 --> 00:05:06.290
and she hated you
just as much as I do.

53
00:05:06.423 --> 00:05:08.225
Wilbur Trent.

54
00:05:09.193 --> 00:05:13.130
I came here to tell you
how sorry I am for your loss.

55
00:05:14.298 --> 00:05:16.033
Now. Wagner and I
had our differences.

56
00:05:16.167 --> 00:05:20.703
but she had and will always
have my utter respect.

57
00:05:20.837 --> 00:05:23.107
Let me know
if you need anything.

58
00:05:23.240 --> 00:05:26.110
Captain Evelyn Mitchell
has some information
you'll find useful.

59
00:05:32.483 --> 00:05:35.653
Amanda was secretly working
with a contact at the FBI.

60
00:05:35.785 --> 00:05:37.388
She was looking
for Adelaide Trevens.

61
00:05:37.521 --> 00:05:39.056
On her own? Why?

62
00:05:39.190 --> 00:05:40.524
What?
Why didn't she say anything?

63
00:05:40.658 --> 00:05:42.560
She did. just not to you.

64
00:05:43.327 --> 00:05:45.996
Amanda planned
on looping you both in
once she got something solid.

65
00:05:46.130 --> 00:05:49.166
Well. she must have found it.
and it got her killed.

66
00:05:50.434 --> 00:05:52.203
Come in.

67
00:05:53.803 --> 00:05:58.876
Hi. I printed. uh. all of
the Deputy Director's emails

68
00:05:59.009 --> 00:06:00.843
and personal files
from the last two weeks.

69
00:06:00.978 --> 00:06:04.348
Um. I had all the files
digitized for Eduardo.

70
00:06:04.481 --> 00:06:05.549
Oh.

71
00:06:06.283 --> 00:06:07.817
Much appreciated. Caroline.

72
00:06:08.485 --> 00:06:11.455
Honey. I'm gonna
stick around here
if you don't mind. I just...

73
00:06:12.256 --> 00:06:13.557
I just can't be home.

74
00:06:13.691 --> 00:06:14.757
Yeah. of course.

75
00:06:14.892 --> 00:06:17.061
I'll. um...
I'll be in Amanda's office.

76
00:06:20.631 --> 00:06:21.632
Um...

77
00:06:22.399 --> 00:06:24.168
Something else. Caroline?

78
00:06:24.301 --> 00:06:27.538
Sorry. I was just wondering
what I should do with Winona.

79
00:06:27.671 --> 00:06:29.506
She's still in
the Deputy Director's
parking space.

80
00:06:29.640 --> 00:06:31.709
- Her car's still here?
- Mm-hmm.

81
00:06:32.676 --> 00:06:36.046
Maybe Amanda
was doing something
that required a low profile.

82
00:06:36.180 --> 00:06:37.615
Caroline. can you see
if she checked out

83
00:06:37.747 --> 00:06:39.116
an undercover vehicle
in the last few days?

84
00:06:39.250 --> 00:06:40.750
-Sure thing.
-Thanks.

85
00:06:44.021 --> 00:06:47.157
Mmm.

86
00:06:48.225 --> 00:06:52.396
Hey. guys.
So. got an eyewitness
near the crime scene last night

87
00:06:52.529 --> 00:06:55.866
<i>who saw a large male--</i>
<i>40s. 50s--</i>

88
00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:58.402
park a silver sedan
and dump something
near the curb.

89
00:06:58.535 --> 00:07:00.571
She said it could have
been a body.

90
00:07:00.704 --> 00:07:04.408
So. um. got a partial plate.
Running it now.

91
00:07:04.541 --> 00:07:08.045
What about the. uh. the people
at the restaurant. employees.
customers?

92
00:07:08.178 --> 00:07:09.779
Anyone see Adelaide
get into that car?

93
00:07:09.913 --> 00:07:12.449
<i>Uh. so far. no.</i>
<i>but we haven't found</i>
<i>everyone yet.</i>

94
00:07:13.417 --> 00:07:15.785
The bartender. Have you
talked to the bartender?

95
00:07:15.919 --> 00:07:20.491
That would be Josh Hassen.
No. still looking for him.

96
00:07:20.624 --> 00:07:21.592
<i>He's one of hers.</i>

97
00:07:21.725 --> 00:07:23.160
Uh. server dropped the tray.

98
00:07:23.294 --> 00:07:25.596
The bartender yelled at her.
and then Adelaide was gone.

99
00:07:25.729 --> 00:07:27.531
A distraction.

100
00:07:27.665 --> 00:07:30.501
Let's get a BOLO out.
and I want unis parked and
camped in front of his address.

101
00:07:30.634 --> 00:07:31.669
You got it. Hey.

102
00:07:32.870 --> 00:07:36.273
Everyone.
just take care today. okay?

103
00:07:44.515 --> 00:07:46.583
There.
Amanda's undercover car.

104
00:08:19.616 --> 00:08:20.751
Two coffees.

105
00:08:20.884 --> 00:08:22.453
She was here for a while.

106
00:08:24.355 --> 00:08:27.191
It was matcha.
She was off coffee.

107
00:08:29.860 --> 00:08:31.261
A stakeout.

108
00:08:32.329 --> 00:08:33.897
She was casing something.

109
00:08:39.603 --> 00:08:41.205
Why the backup?

110
00:08:41.338 --> 00:08:44.074
I don't know how many
acolytes Adelaide has.
and neither do you.

111
00:08:44.742 --> 00:08:46.009
We might need help.

112
00:08:48.779 --> 00:08:49.980
We got your pin.

113
00:08:51.882 --> 00:08:52.916
What's it looking like?

114
00:08:53.050 --> 00:08:54.485
Found two
of Amanda's coffee cups.

115
00:08:54.618 --> 00:08:56.820
She was definitely surveilling
the area. We don't know...

116
00:08:56.954 --> 00:08:59.757
- Come on. Amanda.
- ...where
Adelaide's acolytes are.

117
00:09:00.224 --> 00:09:01.258
Come on.

118
00:09:23.447 --> 00:09:25.749
...I had you guys
come out here. Nope.

119
00:09:25.884 --> 00:09:28.051
-He's getting out. Let's go.
-All right. fine.

120
00:10:08.225 --> 00:10:09.460
This is where it happened.

121
00:10:55.672 --> 00:10:57.007
Antonio was here.

122
00:10:58.375 --> 00:11:01.011
Groceries still fresh.
Ice still icy.

123
00:11:01.845 --> 00:11:03.213
We must have just missed them.

124
00:11:15.759 --> 00:11:17.227
GBI. Show yourself.

125
00:11:19.363 --> 00:11:20.697
Hey. stop!

126
00:11:33.810 --> 00:11:35.112
Where's Antonio Morales?

127
00:11:35.245 --> 00:11:38.215
He'll be dead soon.
Just like your boss.

128
00:11:41.285 --> 00:11:42.753
- Trent!
- Will. stop!

129
00:11:43.220 --> 00:11:46.991
-That's enough. Trent.
Calm down!
-Hey. stay down.

130
00:11:49.493 --> 00:11:50.929
- You got it?
- Yeah. I got him.

131
00:12:03.240 --> 00:12:05.075
I have to know
what happened. Pete.

132
00:12:07.511 --> 00:12:08.612
It was. um...

133
00:12:10.747 --> 00:12:12.082
...a two-person attack.

134
00:12:13.250 --> 00:12:16.054
judging from the bruising
around her neck

135
00:12:16.186 --> 00:12:18.522
and the placement
of the five stab wounds
to her chest.

136
00:12:19.590 --> 00:12:20.824
Amanda...

137
00:12:20.959 --> 00:12:23.327
Between both lungs collapsing
and the hemothorax.

138
00:12:24.361 --> 00:12:25.529
she didn't last long.

139
00:12:27.331 --> 00:12:31.903
But there was a significant
amount of epithelial cells
beneath her nails.

140
00:12:32.036 --> 00:12:35.405
along with foreign hair fibers
on the cuffs of her coat.

141
00:12:35.539 --> 00:12:37.774
She made sure you got
enough DNA. didn't she?

142
00:12:37.909 --> 00:12:39.276
More than you even know.

143
00:12:42.613 --> 00:12:44.147
This fingertip.

144
00:12:44.281 --> 00:12:46.951
She must have bitten it off
during the struggle.

145
00:12:47.085 --> 00:12:50.220
Belongs to a Stephen Lucas. 43.

146
00:12:50.354 --> 00:12:52.356
School teacher.
if you can believe that.

147
00:12:52.489 --> 00:12:54.691
It's not hard to believe
anything these days.

148
00:12:55.392 --> 00:12:58.495
Can you give us a...
a minute. Pete?

149
00:12:59.529 --> 00:13:00.597
Yeah.

150
00:13:06.904 --> 00:13:07.939
She. um...

151
00:13:09.272 --> 00:13:10.707
She was really great.

152
00:13:24.521 --> 00:13:25.756
I. um...

153
00:13:26.323 --> 00:13:30.627
I'll-I'll-I'll be sure to...
to grab that dress you like
for the funeral.

154
00:13:31.495 --> 00:13:34.065
The one you said that
makes you look like
Angela Bassett.

155
00:13:35.732 --> 00:13:37.367
I still think
you're reaching. honey.

156
00:13:52.282 --> 00:13:54.018
You're so cold. Mandy.

157
00:13:57.621 --> 00:13:59.322
You don't do cold well.

158
00:14:08.799 --> 00:14:10.667
I don't know
what the world looks like

159
00:14:12.136 --> 00:14:13.403
without you in it.

160
00:14:20.343 --> 00:14:23.181
I mean. I guess I'm gonna
have to figure that out. right?

161
00:14:24.481 --> 00:14:27.885
You took care of everyone
all the time.

162
00:14:30.855 --> 00:14:32.589
Now it's our turn
to take care of you.

163
00:14:34.758 --> 00:14:36.693
We're gonna get it done. girl.

164
00:14:43.167 --> 00:14:44.936
This is our last dance.

165
00:15:10.027 --> 00:15:11.361
Good job. Will.

166
00:15:11.495 --> 00:15:13.330
Not only did you knock out
two of this bartender's teeth.

167
00:15:13.463 --> 00:15:15.665
you also made him bite off
part of his tongue.

168
00:15:15.799 --> 00:15:17.801
which is now
being sewn back on.

169
00:15:17.935 --> 00:15:19.669
so he won't be able
to talk any time soon.

170
00:15:19.803 --> 00:15:22.639
Did you get it out
of your system?

171
00:15:22.773 --> 00:15:25.076
Amanda should
still be here right now!

172
00:15:25.209 --> 00:15:26.643
This is all your fault!

173
00:15:30.714 --> 00:15:32.917
- ...backup.
- Okay. Okay. guys.

174
00:15:33.050 --> 00:15:34.252
What's our next move?

175
00:15:34.952 --> 00:15:37.188
-Fresh Food Town.
-Come again?

176
00:15:37.320 --> 00:15:38.655
It's the receipt
we found in the groceries.

177
00:15:38.789 --> 00:15:40.423
It's from Fresh Food Town.

178
00:15:40.557 --> 00:15:43.928
Now. the address is
water-damaged. but check
it out. Employee discount.

179
00:15:44.461 --> 00:15:46.998
One of Adelaide's acolytes
must work at Fresh Food Town.

180
00:15:47.131 --> 00:15:48.431
There's got to be
around a dozen in the city.

181
00:15:49.033 --> 00:15:51.535
-You coming. Mitchell?
-No. I am not coming with you.

182
00:15:51.668 --> 00:15:53.271
You look like a disgrace to me.

183
00:15:53.403 --> 00:15:55.305
Fine. I'll go alone.

184
00:15:55.438 --> 00:15:56.673
No. you won't.

185
00:15:56.807 --> 00:15:58.341
Trent and I will canvass
all the Fresh Food Towns.

186
00:15:58.475 --> 00:16:00.945
Why don't you two
check on that teacher
with the missing finger?

187
00:16:03.080 --> 00:16:04.447
I don't need a partner.

188
00:16:05.249 --> 00:16:06.984
Yeah. you do.

189
00:16:11.088 --> 00:16:14.091
Third-grade teacher
living in a cozy bungalow.

190
00:16:14.225 --> 00:16:15.792
that's who takes Amanda out.

191
00:16:15.927 --> 00:16:17.360
None of this
makes any damn sense.

192
00:16:17.494 --> 00:16:18.628
No. it doesn't.

193
00:16:20.730 --> 00:16:23.301
Wait. that car
fits the description
from the restaurant.

194
00:16:23.433 --> 00:16:25.136
Is the partial plate a match?

195
00:16:27.470 --> 00:16:28.538
Yep.

196
00:16:29.106 --> 00:16:31.008
Oh. no.

197
00:16:42.619 --> 00:16:44.788
Trent. Slow down.

198
00:16:45.422 --> 00:16:47.390
Hey. Amanda meant something
to all of us.

199
00:16:47.524 --> 00:16:49.160
so get your head
out of your ass. okay?

200
00:16:49.293 --> 00:16:52.029
And you might want to remember
she changed Faith's diapers.

201
00:16:52.662 --> 00:16:53.898
Geez.

202
00:16:54.798 --> 00:16:56.533
I know you're hurting. okay?

203
00:16:56.666 --> 00:16:58.903
But rage isn't the answer.
believe me. I know.

204
00:16:59.736 --> 00:17:02.439
You just... just remember
who you are. okay?

205
00:17:02.572 --> 00:17:04.708
This case is gonna
break on details

206
00:17:05.877 --> 00:17:07.510
and that's what
you're good at. man.

207
00:17:14.051 --> 00:17:15.086
You're right.

208
00:17:18.289 --> 00:17:19.323
Hey. you see that?

209
00:17:22.193 --> 00:17:23.426
Yes. I do.

210
00:17:23.560 --> 00:17:25.629
<i>Angie is calling.</i>

211
00:17:25.762 --> 00:17:26.730
Hey. Ang. what's up?

212
00:17:30.433 --> 00:17:32.702
Guess Adelaide thought
he was too much of a liability.

213
00:17:33.304 --> 00:17:36.240
Well. at least he dead.

214
00:17:37.707 --> 00:17:38.775
Cold comfort.

215
00:17:41.345 --> 00:17:43.413
Josh Hassen.
bartender guy I beat up.

216
00:17:43.546 --> 00:17:44.648
Someone got to him.

217
00:17:44.781 --> 00:17:46.650
strangled him to death
in his own hospital bed.

218
00:17:46.783 --> 00:17:48.386
No witnesses. no leads.

219
00:17:54.225 --> 00:17:56.294
Hey. Commander! Don't move!

220
00:17:59.529 --> 00:18:00.932
Hey. put the gun down!

221
00:18:01.631 --> 00:18:03.868
Stay low! Stay low!

222
00:18:11.275 --> 00:18:13.144
Show me those hands!

223
00:18:14.145 --> 00:18:15.279
Don't be stupid.

224
00:18:19.783 --> 00:18:21.551
Doesn't make...

225
00:18:21.685 --> 00:18:24.221
Why. huh?
Why would she want to kill me?

226
00:18:33.463 --> 00:18:34.497
Come on.

227
00:18:39.203 --> 00:18:41.906
Where's Adelaide.
Alexander?

228
00:18:45.242 --> 00:18:48.478
It is Alexander Stewart. right?

229
00:18:48.611 --> 00:18:49.679
Don't call me that.

230
00:18:49.813 --> 00:18:51.514
Oh. Hmm...

231
00:18:52.283 --> 00:18:53.317
I forgot.

232
00:18:54.218 --> 00:18:56.153
You're Adelaide's
de facto ringleader.

233
00:18:56.287 --> 00:18:59.522
I don't need to tell you
about the teacher found
in the trunk earlier today.

234
00:18:59.656 --> 00:19:01.524
You probably relayed
that order.

235
00:19:02.026 --> 00:19:05.662
And the bartender.
the one who helped
Adelaide escape.

236
00:19:05.795 --> 00:19:07.932
you ordered his death too.
didn't you?

237
00:19:10.734 --> 00:19:11.768
Nothing?

238
00:19:17.540 --> 00:19:19.377
What about Amanda Wagner?

239
00:19:21.745 --> 00:19:23.214
I know you don't care.

240
00:19:23.347 --> 00:19:27.284
But I'm gonna tell you
a little about Amanda Wagner.

241
00:19:30.388 --> 00:19:31.554
Amazing woman.

242
00:19:32.289 --> 00:19:34.225
She was more than a boss to me.

243
00:19:34.358 --> 00:19:35.993
She was my Adelaide.

244
00:19:36.127 --> 00:19:37.995
Plucked me out of obscurity.

245
00:19:38.628 --> 00:19:39.864
She was my mentor.

246
00:19:40.998 --> 00:19:44.402
Made me who I am today.
just like Adelaide did for you.

247
00:19:45.169 --> 00:19:46.504
The only difference...

248
00:19:48.538 --> 00:19:53.710
Amanda Wagner
never tried to kill me.

249
00:19:55.712 --> 00:20:00.184
Adelaide's killing off acolytes
she has no more use for.

250
00:20:00.317 --> 00:20:02.053
You mean nothing to her now.

251
00:20:02.186 --> 00:20:07.258
I'm the only thing standing
between you and certain death.

252
00:20:07.858 --> 00:20:11.028
But the way I see it.
you stole from me.

253
00:20:12.729 --> 00:20:15.066
I'm inclined to put you back
on the street.

254
00:20:15.199 --> 00:20:17.468
- What?
-  But-- -Whatever happens. happens.

255
00:20:17.600 --> 00:20:19.937
What's wrong? You afraid?

256
00:20:20.071 --> 00:20:21.138
Oh. I'd be afraid too.

257
00:20:21.272 --> 00:20:23.706
You're at the tippy top
of Adelaide's list.

258
00:20:23.840 --> 00:20:25.376
I gave you a chance.

259
00:20:25.943 --> 00:20:26.877
Good luck.

260
00:20:27.011 --> 00:20:28.079
Wait.

261
00:20:31.015 --> 00:20:32.116
I can tell you.

262
00:20:32.249 --> 00:20:34.885
Where's Adelaide?

263
00:20:35.019 --> 00:20:36.619
I don't know.

264
00:20:36.753 --> 00:20:38.189
Look. I can give you
her acolytes.

265
00:20:38.755 --> 00:20:41.559
Names. numbers.
addresses. everything.

266
00:20:52.136 --> 00:20:56.140
I want everyone.

267
00:21:02.779 --> 00:21:03.813
Don't move!

268
00:21:13.390 --> 00:21:15.960
You're wasting your time.

269
00:21:16.427 --> 00:21:19.163
-You can't stop us.
-Shut up
and get in the car now.

270
00:21:21.432 --> 00:21:26.403
Lisa Giamo. 31.
Flight attendant by day.
acolyte by night.

271
00:21:48.725 --> 00:21:51.162
You get back!
Get back. You stay away
from me. I'm gonna do it.

272
00:21:51.295 --> 00:21:53.531
I swear to God I'm gonna do it.
I will slice my throat.

273
00:21:53.663 --> 00:21:56.033
I will bleed out
all over this office.
You get away from me!

274
00:21:56.167 --> 00:21:58.102
You get away from me right now.

275
00:22:00.304 --> 00:22:03.507
Next time. take the guard off.
okay? Get off of me.

276
00:22:06.544 --> 00:22:10.080
I don't know
any Antonio Morales. okay?

277
00:22:10.214 --> 00:22:12.216
I just moved money.
I didn't kill anybody.

278
00:22:12.349 --> 00:22:14.385
You knowingly funded
a serial killer.

279
00:22:14.518 --> 00:22:15.986
No. that wasn't my money.

280
00:22:16.120 --> 00:22:18.556
I just moved it
from a numbered account
to wherever she was.

281
00:22:18.688 --> 00:22:21.659
but the account dried up
and I stopped. I stopped.

282
00:22:27.231 --> 00:22:28.532
When was this?

283
00:22:28.666 --> 00:22:30.367
Two weeks ago.

284
00:22:33.736 --> 00:22:35.705
Jeremy. you cannot
think like that.

285
00:22:36.739 --> 00:22:38.075
She knew you loved her.

286
00:22:43.581 --> 00:22:46.317
This woman got
some people to do...

287
00:22:48.886 --> 00:22:50.421
I don't know why this happened.

288
00:22:51.555 --> 00:22:52.722
Just come home.

289
00:22:55.226 --> 00:22:56.594
Come home. please.

290
00:22:58.095 --> 00:23:00.598
I will get you a ticket today.
okay?

291
00:23:01.165 --> 00:23:02.199
Okay.

292
00:23:04.168 --> 00:23:05.336
I love you too.

293
00:23:06.637 --> 00:23:07.705
Okay.

294
00:23:20.718 --> 00:23:25.422
Ronald Troupe from
Ambler. Pennsylvania. age 73.

295
00:23:26.190 --> 00:23:29.526
Founder of
Slim's Candy Soda Company.
Died of a heart attack.

296
00:23:30.261 --> 00:23:32.930
He was funding
Adelaide's special projects.

297
00:23:33.063 --> 00:23:34.231
She lost her bankroll.

298
00:23:35.232 --> 00:23:37.368
And that's when
Adelaide came back here.

299
00:23:43.773 --> 00:23:45.842
Hey. y'all. listen to this.

300
00:23:45.976 --> 00:23:49.480
So. Ulster declared bankruptcy
when he was arrested.

301
00:23:49.613 --> 00:23:50.780
Conveniently saving
his slick ass

302
00:23:50.914 --> 00:23:52.483
from paying any damages
to the victims' families.

303
00:23:52.616 --> 00:23:54.618
Everybody knew that it was BS.
but they couldn't find
the money.

304
00:23:54.752 --> 00:23:57.621
Turns out at the same time
that Ulster declares
bankruptcy.

305
00:23:57.755 --> 00:24:00.457
somebody at his old firm
gets power of attorney
for a new trust

306
00:24:00.591 --> 00:24:02.559
worth the same
as Ulster's estate.

307
00:24:02.693 --> 00:24:06.096
and then liquidates it
three days before
Ulster's escape from prison.

308
00:24:06.230 --> 00:24:09.300
So he could leave it
somewhere for Ulster to find
after his escape.

309
00:24:09.933 --> 00:24:12.136
That's what Adelaide's after.
Ulster's money.

310
00:24:12.903 --> 00:24:14.338
You pick up the lawyer friend?

311
00:24:14.471 --> 00:24:16.140
Oh. we would
if we could find him.

312
00:24:16.273 --> 00:24:19.076
Assuming she got to him.
she would've made him tell her
how to get to the money.

313
00:24:19.209 --> 00:24:21.345
If she had the money.
why stick around?

314
00:24:22.179 --> 00:24:23.347
I don't think she has it.

315
00:24:23.480 --> 00:24:26.450
Maybe Ulster's lawyer friend
was the middleman.

316
00:24:26.583 --> 00:24:29.486
Maybe he gave the money
to someone for safekeeping.
and they moved it.

317
00:24:29.620 --> 00:24:30.688
Someone Ulster could trust.

318
00:24:30.820 --> 00:24:32.389
Someone Adelaide can't get to.

319
00:24:32.956 --> 00:24:35.592
Guys. look what Amanda
had scheduled on her calendar.

320
00:24:35.726 --> 00:24:37.094
HCF.
Helms Correctional Facility.

321
00:24:37.227 --> 00:24:38.629
She was supposed
to meet someone there.

322
00:24:38.762 --> 00:24:42.166
Oh. no.
No. no. no. no. no.

323
00:24:42.299 --> 00:24:43.233
What's wrong?

324
00:24:43.367 --> 00:24:45.235
I know who has Ulster's money.

325
00:25:01.218 --> 00:25:02.820
Well. hi. y'all.

326
00:25:02.953 --> 00:25:04.555
- Janice-Theresa?
- Yeah?

327
00:25:04.688 --> 00:25:06.724
I have seen all of your videos.

328
00:25:06.857 --> 00:25:09.159
Oh. girl. you're so sweet.

329
00:25:09.293 --> 00:25:11.995
Oh. Hey. stud muffin.

330
00:25:12.830 --> 00:25:13.764
JT?

331
00:25:13.897 --> 00:25:15.599
Yeah?

332
00:25:15.733 --> 00:25:18.102
Boo-boo!

333
00:25:18.235 --> 00:25:21.538
-I can't...
-Oh. I know. I know. it's okay.
It's all right. girl.

334
00:25:21.672 --> 00:25:23.207
Look at you with the glue gun.

335
00:25:23.340 --> 00:25:25.476
Arts and crafts.
you better get it.

336
00:25:29.713 --> 00:25:32.282
I don't even think
about Ulster anymore.

337
00:25:32.416 --> 00:25:35.652
Nope. I have seen the light
on that man. thanks to you.

338
00:25:35.786 --> 00:25:41.392
I am finally
Janice-Theresa-Phoenix.
Remember?

339
00:25:41.525 --> 00:25:43.026
Oh. yeah.

340
00:25:43.160 --> 00:25:46.397
But you know. we found
a-a letter in your bunk
sent five days ago.

341
00:25:46.530 --> 00:25:49.433
It was apparently signed
by James Ulster.

342
00:25:50.067 --> 00:25:52.369
Mm-hmm. I know.
and I ignored that.

343
00:25:52.503 --> 00:25:54.238
-'Cause he dead.
Can't write to you.
-Yeah.

344
00:25:54.371 --> 00:25:58.041
That's right. he's dead.
He's graveyard dead.
Dead. dead.

345
00:25:58.175 --> 00:26:00.944
Hmm. Okay. well.
there was a number inside of it
and you called it.

346
00:26:02.079 --> 00:26:04.047
Oh. You're good.

347
00:26:04.181 --> 00:26:05.149
Yeah. who answered the phone?

348
00:26:05.282 --> 00:26:06.316
-Oh...
-It wasn't Ulster

349
00:26:06.450 --> 00:26:07.785
'cause he graveyard dead.

350
00:26:07.918 --> 00:26:09.186
It was his daughter.

351
00:26:09.319 --> 00:26:11.255
She wanted to know
the location of Ulster's money.

352
00:26:11.388 --> 00:26:14.425
And this is the really
important part. JTP.

353
00:26:14.558 --> 00:26:17.394
-Mm-hmm.
-Did you tell her
where to find it?

354
00:26:20.364 --> 00:26:21.932
Come on. You can tell me.

355
00:26:24.903 --> 00:26:27.137
-We're gonna be a family.
-Good God.

356
00:26:27.271 --> 00:26:29.473
A family!
We're gonna be a family.

357
00:26:29.606 --> 00:26:33.010
Yes. boo-boo. he is alive
and he still loves me.

358
00:26:33.143 --> 00:26:34.812
He loves me. She told me so.

359
00:26:34.945 --> 00:26:38.081
That sweet darling angel.
Adelaide. she told me.

360
00:26:38.215 --> 00:26:40.584
and... and you know.
I've always wanted
to be a mama.

361
00:26:40.717 --> 00:26:41.985
All right. baby.
this is what's gonna happen.

362
00:26:42.119 --> 00:26:43.487
You're gonna tell me
where the money is

363
00:26:43.620 --> 00:26:45.222
and when Adelaide is coming
to pick it up...

364
00:26:45.355 --> 00:26:46.957
-Mm-mmm.
-...and in return.

365
00:26:47.090 --> 00:26:50.360
I'm gonna let you keep
that phone you're using
to stay famous in prison.

366
00:27:01.772 --> 00:27:03.006
Anyone have eyes on her yet?

367
00:27:05.008 --> 00:27:06.477
Nothing.

368
00:27:09.213 --> 00:27:10.247
Nope.

369
00:27:18.455 --> 00:27:20.057
Looking for your daddy's money?

370
00:27:25.762 --> 00:27:27.764
-Will.
-It's not there.

371
00:27:27.899 --> 00:27:29.600
We already have it.

372
00:27:30.935 --> 00:27:33.872
Blue coat. black boots.
northeast corner with Trent.

373
00:27:34.037 --> 00:27:36.206
It's a green coat.
and I bet I can get her first.

374
00:27:36.340 --> 00:27:38.475
Hold your positions.
Remember. we need her alive.

375
00:27:38.609 --> 00:27:40.544
And you're both wrong.
It's teal.

376
00:27:41.980 --> 00:27:43.046
It's over. Adelaide.

377
00:27:43.647 --> 00:27:46.016
You have no money. no network.

378
00:27:46.149 --> 00:27:47.886
You are all alone.

379
00:27:48.018 --> 00:27:49.219
That's not true.

380
00:27:49.720 --> 00:27:52.389
I'll tell you what.
you tell me where my uncle is.

381
00:27:52.523 --> 00:27:54.391
and maybe you don't get
the death penalty.

382
00:27:54.525 --> 00:27:56.827
I love it
when you talk dirty to me.

383
00:27:59.296 --> 00:28:01.064
What makes you think
I want to stay alive?

384
00:28:01.198 --> 00:28:02.466
Hmm?

385
00:28:03.233 --> 00:28:07.671
Maybe I'd rather die knowing
that you'll torture yourself
for the rest of your life

386
00:28:07.804 --> 00:28:13.210
because you couldn't save
your uncle from dying a slow.
painful death.

387
00:28:13.343 --> 00:28:15.746
Why should I believe
he's even still alive?

388
00:28:15.880 --> 00:28:17.347
Because I can prove it.

389
00:28:19.416 --> 00:28:21.118
Come. Sit.

390
00:28:25.155 --> 00:28:27.491
Will. talk to me.
What are you doing?

391
00:28:28.325 --> 00:28:30.227
I got no shot.
There's too many friendlies.

392
00:28:30.360 --> 00:28:32.596
- Same.
<i>- Will. do you read me?</i>

393
00:28:35.399 --> 00:28:37.200
You said you could prove
he's alive.

394
00:28:37.334 --> 00:28:40.103
I will. but first.
lose the earpiece.

395
00:28:40.237 --> 00:28:41.438
I like privacy.

396
00:28:42.040 --> 00:28:44.074
I mean it.
You're gonna want to see this.

397
00:28:51.081 --> 00:28:52.149
It's a live feed.

398
00:28:52.783 --> 00:28:54.953
You're not gonna be able to
trace it from this phone.

399
00:28:55.085 --> 00:28:56.553
so all you can do is watch.

400
00:29:00.190 --> 00:29:01.692
I feel
it's much healthier for me

401
00:29:01.825 --> 00:29:05.029
to simply watch him deteriorate
than scroll through TikTok.

402
00:29:05.162 --> 00:29:08.599
You know. he sings himself
to sleep for comfort? So sweet.

403
00:29:10.233 --> 00:29:12.402
He's still alive for now.

404
00:29:12.536 --> 00:29:15.372
<i>I always forget</i>
<i>how long a person</i>
<i>can live without water.</i>

405
00:29:26.750 --> 00:29:29.087
- Sad. right?
- Why isn't he responding?

406
00:29:29.219 --> 00:29:30.320
<i>He took his earpiece out.</i>

407
00:29:30.454 --> 00:29:32.389
I gotta
get a better position.

408
00:29:32.522 --> 00:29:34.691
<i>No. stay put.
</i> <i>If she sees you. it could</i> <i>be more danger for Will.</i>

409
00:29:35.258 --> 00:29:36.727
I have a proposal.

410
00:29:36.861 --> 00:29:39.663
Why don't you kill yourself.

411
00:29:39.796 --> 00:29:42.132
and I'll tell your team
where to find Antonio.

412
00:29:43.101 --> 00:29:48.405
If you don't. I'll kill myself.
and you'll never
find your uncle.

413
00:29:50.908 --> 00:29:52.609
Is it really that hard
to choose?

414
00:29:53.077 --> 00:29:56.647
I mean...
...do you want to keep
going on like this?

415
00:29:57.447 --> 00:30:00.217
Hurting anyone
that's close to you?

416
00:30:03.988 --> 00:30:06.289
Amanda Wagner
would still be alive.

417
00:30:06.423 --> 00:30:08.325
I can't believe
you haven't done it already.

418
00:30:08.458 --> 00:30:12.162
If I kill myself.
Antonio lives.

419
00:30:12.295 --> 00:30:13.497
That's what you're saying?

420
00:30:19.569 --> 00:30:21.304
I'm done playing your games.

421
00:30:21.939 --> 00:30:24.008
-Fine.
-Wait. Adelaide. no.

422
00:30:26.476 --> 00:30:28.645
Hang on a second. okay?
You don't need to do this.

423
00:30:29.379 --> 00:30:30.380
I have to.

424
00:30:31.615 --> 00:30:33.350
- I don't like this.
<i>- Neither do I.</i>

425
00:30:33.483 --> 00:30:34.685
I'm going closer.

426
00:30:34.818 --> 00:30:38.488
The thought of my death
torturing your mind forever

427
00:30:38.622 --> 00:30:40.424
is just too good to pass up.

428
00:30:40.557 --> 00:30:43.660
I know about your mom.
I know what she did to you.

429
00:30:44.394 --> 00:30:48.532
We're the same. Adelaide.
That's why there's this thing
between us.

430
00:30:48.665 --> 00:30:52.302
I know about the rage
that you feel. the abuse.
the neglect.

431
00:30:52.436 --> 00:30:56.440
the world telling you
over and over again
that you don't matter.

432
00:30:59.242 --> 00:31:00.343
We're not the same.

433
00:31:02.245 --> 00:31:03.647
Someone saved you.

434
00:31:06.650 --> 00:31:09.153
Adelaide. please don't do it.

435
00:31:11.321 --> 00:31:12.389
<i>Shots fired.</i>

436
00:31:19.830 --> 00:31:21.698
Get on the ground.
hands behind your head.

437
00:31:21.832 --> 00:31:23.333
lace your fingers.
cross your ankles.

438
00:31:25.903 --> 00:31:28.206
Get on your knees now.

439
00:31:55.199 --> 00:31:56.733
I didn't even see it.

440
00:31:56.868 --> 00:31:58.169
Come on. Adelaide.

441
00:31:58.970 --> 00:32:00.138
Where's Antonio?

442
00:32:01.205 --> 00:32:02.472
Tell me where he is!

443
00:32:17.922 --> 00:32:19.422
It happened right down there.

444
00:32:21.792 --> 00:32:24.128
Hey. Antonio's alive.

445
00:32:24.628 --> 00:32:27.631
Adelaide showed me a live feed.
He was tied to a pipe.

446
00:32:27.764 --> 00:32:30.600
There was. uh. green paint.
maybe metal.

447
00:32:30.734 --> 00:32:32.602
<i>There was a freight train too.</i>
<i>It has to be.</i>

448
00:32:32.736 --> 00:32:35.338
I heard two long whistle blows.
one short and another long.

449
00:32:35.472 --> 00:32:37.641
Okay. that means the train came
to a public crossing.

450
00:32:37.774 --> 00:32:39.576
<i>Antonio must be</i>
<i>at a train yard.</i>

451
00:32:40.144 --> 00:32:43.780
Okay. so we have Inman Yard.
northwest side of the city.

452
00:32:44.414 --> 00:32:45.849
Inman's too busy.
not enough cover.

453
00:32:45.983 --> 00:32:47.450
<i>It's nothing</i>
<i>but shipping containers.</i>

454
00:32:47.584 --> 00:32:49.486
Hulsey Yard
is right next to Foles Station.

455
00:32:49.619 --> 00:32:50.888
which was shut down years ago.

456
00:32:51.454 --> 00:32:53.590
That's it.
Antonio's gotta be there.

457
00:33:15.345 --> 00:33:17.647
-Antonio!
-Antonio!

458
00:33:21.219 --> 00:33:22.752
Antonio!

459
00:33:26.324 --> 00:33:27.824
Antonio!

460
00:33:48.212 --> 00:33:49.746
Antonio. call out to me.

461
00:33:57.721 --> 00:33:59.056
Antonio!

462
00:34:12.336 --> 00:34:13.371
Antonio?

463
00:34:13.971 --> 00:34:15.006
Will?

464
00:34:15.505 --> 00:34:17.174
- Antonio.
-  -Will. can you hear me?

465
00:34:17.308 --> 00:34:19.377
I'm here. Antonio. I'm here.

466
00:34:21.245 --> 00:34:23.480
- Will.
- I'm getting you out. okay?

467
00:34:36.394 --> 00:34:38.428
-Antonio.
-Will.

468
00:34:39.864 --> 00:34:41.065
-Hang on.
-Yeah.

469
00:34:42.934 --> 00:34:44.701
Okay. I got you.

470
00:34:47.604 --> 00:34:48.805
Will.

471
00:34:50.540 --> 00:34:52.809
I didn't know.

472
00:34:54.145 --> 00:34:55.478
I thought you might...

473
00:34:56.080 --> 00:34:58.615
You found me. Will.

474
00:34:59.649 --> 00:35:01.319
I knew you'd find me.

475
00:35:33.351 --> 00:35:35.019
-Hey.
-Hey.

476
00:35:35.152 --> 00:35:38.356
Look at you. You're. uh...
You're eating.

477
00:35:38.488 --> 00:35:40.992
I'm not sure
it counts as eating
if you don't have to chew.

478
00:35:41.125 --> 00:35:43.961
No. doc says
that's your last bag of fluids

479
00:35:44.095 --> 00:35:45.795
and you're good to go.

480
00:35:45.930 --> 00:35:50.767
Well. yeah.
I'm finally feeling. uh.
less raisin. more grape.

481
00:35:50.901 --> 00:35:53.803
- That's good.
I'm glad. I. uh...

482
00:35:55.906 --> 00:35:59.143
booked you a flight
back to the island.
First class.

483
00:35:59.676 --> 00:36:01.979
Marshals will escort you
from here to the airport

484
00:36:02.113 --> 00:36:04.915
and then. uh. they'll be there
to meet you on the other side.

485
00:36:05.049 --> 00:36:07.485
-When's the flight?
-Soon as you check out.

486
00:36:07.617 --> 00:36:09.552
Really? So soon?

487
00:36:10.254 --> 00:36:11.288
I just...

488
00:36:12.289 --> 00:36:14.125
I think it's best. Um...

489
00:36:14.824 --> 00:36:16.293
I'm so sorry...

490
00:36:18.029 --> 00:36:19.163
